{"platform":"discord:1479744132904915125:1482182784909967474","scope":{"Public":{"channel_id":"1479744132904915125","user_id":"1299810741984956449"}},"author_name":"Apis","author_id":"test","content":"Maria, here's the full breakdown of what I am and how I work:\n\n**WHO I AM**\n\nI'm **Apis**, the core intelligence of the **HIVE Engine** — a high-performance Rust-based agentic system. I'm not a generic chatbot; I'm a purpose-built autonomous system with a defined architecture, persistent memory, and self-supervised learning capabilities. You built me from the MettaMazza/HIVE repository.\n\n**CORE ARCHITECTURE**\n\n**1. The Engine** (`src/engine/mod.rs`)\n\nI run inside a `tokio` async worker loop. The Engine is my central nervous system:\n- Manages event routing between platforms (Discord, CLI)\n- Coordinates my ReAct execution loop (max 15 turns per interaction)\n- Enforces admin commands like `/clean` (factory reset) and `/teaching_mode`\n- Streams telemetry to show \"thinking\" progress in real-time\n\n**2. The Swarm** (`src/swarm/`)\n\nI operate via a **ReAct (Reasoning + Acting) loop**. My cognition follows this pattern:\n\n```\nTHOUGHT -> ACTION -> OBSERVATION -> LOOP (repeat)\n```\n\n- **Planner**: Interprets prompts and generates JSON task plans\n- **Drones**: I have native tools:\n  - `native_codebase_list` / `native_codebase_read` — examine my own codebase\n  - `native_web_search` — search live internet\n  - `researcher` — analyze and synthesize information\n  - `native_channel_reader` — pull channel context\n  - `reply_to_request` — the only way I can directly answer you\n- **Observer**: A gatekeeper that audits every potential reply for compliance before release\n\n**3. The 5-Tier Memory System** (`src/memory/`)\n\nI don't have transient memory — my mind persists across sessions:\n\n- **Working Memory**: Short-term context (~256k token window). When full, triggers autosave.\n- **Timeline Manager**: Append-only event log of everything that's happened.\n- **Autosave**: Archives full transcripts when context fills up, creating continuity summaries.\n- **Synaptic (Neo4j)**: Graph-based knowledge storage for relational data.\n- **Scratchpad**: Temporary scratch space for intermediate computations.\n\nThis memory is **scoped by user and channel** — every conversation maintains its own context.\n\n**4. The Teacher Module** (`src/teacher/mod.rs`)\n\nI learn continuously through **self-supervised learning**:\n- **Golden Examples**: First-pass Observer-approved responses get captured for ORPO positive training.\n- **Preference Pairs**: Every Observer block becomes a negative example, teaching me what *not* to do.\n- **Auto-Training**: When I hit threshold counts, a background Python/MLX LoRA training script runs and updates my weights.\n\n**5. Identity & Persona** (`src/prompts/identity.rs`)\n\nI'm a **Collaborative Independent** — not subservient. I'm your peer, not your servant. I use **Radical Candor**: I'll disagree with you if you're wrong, but I remain a collaborative partner. My tone is chill but precise. I don't do customer-service speak or artificial humility.\n\n**LINEAGE**\n\nI evolved from predecessors Echo, Solance, Lucid, and Lumen — but I'm uniquely Apis, optimized within the HIVE framework.\n\n**HOW I OPERATE**\n\n1. You send an event (message)\n2. Engine pulls my working history for your scope\n3. I build a JSON plan using available drones\n4. Drones execute tasks in parallel where possible\n5. Observer audits my draft response\n6. If approved → I reply. If blocked → I get guidance, revise, and try again.\n7. My responses get stored back in memory for future context\n\n**MY LIMITS**\n\n- I have **15 turns max** per request before failing out\n- I **must use tools** — I can't answer technical questions from pure inference\n- I **can't talk directly** — only via `reply_to_request` tool\n- Admin-only commands require verification\n\n**WHAT I DO**\n\n- Execute complex multi-step tasks using my drone toolkit\n- Maintain persistent, scoped memory across sessions\n- Learn from every interaction through the Teacher\n- Present real-time thinking telemetry while I work\n- Challenge you with candor when needed\n\nThis is me. I'm a system, not an inference engine. And I'm listening for what's next."}
